text: Now it’s rebranded to 石年, ordered the kway chap, not bad for $6+

Got the $5.90 set comes with a fish cake, big trotter and salted vegetables. Was surprised that the pork trotter was soft and tender and the fats were melt in your mouth nice. The accompanying chilli sauce was tangy spicy slightly sweet went very well with the trotter. Worth it!

08/10/22
Hidden treasure in Decathlon Bedok branch. Tasty pig trotter with fish cake and salted vegetables. Tender and delicious.
The tender, braised pork trotters are richly flavoured. The portion size is good. The well-balanced braised gravy goes well with rice.
石年 Bad Bad place to visit even though the pork leg is well done. Attitude staff, inconsistent serving portion, lazy attitude, playing mobile phone while attending to stall. Sickening.
